From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 10:45:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] mmdevapi: Prioritize active DualSense mono endpoints.

Spider-Man Remastered discovers the controller speaker through normal render
endpoint enumeration, then opens that speaker endpoint directly for controller
effect audio. After hiding stale DualSense mono endpoints and skipping fake PnP
AudioEndpoint registration to avoid the main-menu crash, the active controller
speaker can end up late enough in the collection that the game does not choose
it.

Keep the normal default render endpoint first, but list active DualSense and
DualSense Edge mono speaker endpoints immediately after it. Stale/not-present
controller speaker endpoints remain hidden, and hotplugged controllers are
still treated as new endpoints instead of reconnecting stale devices.
---
 dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
index 2fb7a2e0b57..dfe3f2a2664 100644
--- a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
+++ b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
@@ -741,7 +741,7 @@ static BOOL should_hide_from_endpoint_collection(const MMDevice *device)
 
 static BOOL should_prioritize_dualsense_mono_endpoint(const MMDevice *device)
 {
-    return FALSE;
+    return is_dualsense_mono_endpoint(device) && (device->state & DEVICE_STATE_ACTIVE);
 }
 
 static BOOL collection_device_visible(const MMDevice *device, EDataFlow flow, DWORD state)
